{"id": "927d909a-3357-4ad8-b3b7-87d89ee0335f", "url": "http://ipt.iobis.org/obiscanada/resource?r=mcgill_curtis1970msc", "archive": "https://ipt.iobis.org/obiscanada/archive.do?r=mcgill_curtis1970msc", "published": "2021-04-16T11:03:11.000Z", "created": null, "updated": "2025-11-12T23:47:38.709Z", "core": "occurrence", "extensions": [], "statistics": {"Event": 0, "absence": 0, "dropped": 0, "Occurrence": 1845, "DNADerivedData": 0, "MeasurementOrFact": 0}, "extent": "POLYGON((-86.3333 81.05,-76.9167 81.05,-76.9167 81.4167,-86.3333 81.4167,-86.3333 81.05))", "title": "McGill University: Depth distributions of benthic polychaetes in two fjords on Ellesmere Island, NWT.", "citation": "Curtis, M.A. (2018) McGill University: Depth distributions of benthic polychaetes in two fjords on Ellesmere Island, NWT. Version 1 In OBIS Canada Digital Collections. Bedford Institute of Oceanography, Dartmouth, NS, Canada. Published by OBIS, Digital http://www.iobis.org/. Accessed on \u2013INSERT DATE", "citation_id": null, "abstract": "As part of a McGill University thesis project, grab samples were collected from two fiords on Ellesmere Island, NWT during two summer. Replicate samples were collected from various depths along a transect extending out from the shore with the objective of determining depth distributions of benthic polychaetes in the two fjords.\nVersion 1 of this dataset includes presence information for the dominant taxa. This information was extracted from thesis appendices (Curtis 1970). Nominal latitude and longitude coordinates have been assigned to this dataset as the exact locations where the grab samples were collected was not provided.", "intellectualrights": "This work is licensed under a  Creative Commons Attribution (CC-BY) 4.0 License", "feed": {"id": "6ae5ad4f-2a01-43bd-9fb4-cc9c7f38f105", "url": "http://ipt.vliz.be/obiscanada/rss.do"}, "institutes": [{"name": "Fisheries and Oceans Canada \u2013 Bedford Institute of Oceanography", "oceanexpert_id": 5070, "o